{"article_id":"gjjoizT9GOciopHk","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"a path to citizenship for those","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"who arrived in the country illegally as children","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"a plan","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"to legalize undocumented workers","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"who have American family ties or sponsoring employers","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"House Republicans","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"led by Speaker John Boehner","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"are preparing to unveil a major immigration initiative this week","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that many hope","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"could trigger movement on an issue","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that has troubled the nation for decades.","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"The brief outline of immigration principles","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Boehner will unveil at a three-day Republican leadership retreat in Cambridge , Md. ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"will include strengthening border security and creating new visas for foreign workers ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"and offer a path to legalization","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"- though not necessarily citizenship -","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"for the nation ' s 11 million to 12 million undocumented immigrants ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"according to people","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"briefed on the deliberations","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"who spoke to The New York Times and The Washington Post .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Coming on the week of President Barack Obama 's `` State of the Union '' address ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"which will be given Tuesday night ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"some Democrats are expressing hope","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that new momentum could yield results","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"after months","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"in which the issue languished in the House.","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"On Sunday ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"speaking on NBC 's `` Meet the Press , ''","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul said","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"there is some room for compromise on immigration with the Obama administration .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"`` We don ' t agree on the whole comprehensive package with the Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"but I ' ll bet you","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"about half of it","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"we agree on , ''","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Paul said .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"`` The question is :","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"are we willing to narrow our focus","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and go after things","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"that we can agree to","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"and get them done ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"or are we going to stay so polarized","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"that we always have to have our way or the highway ? \"","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Administration officials and others told the Post","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"that there still is a long way to go","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"before any compromise could be reached between the House and Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"which approved a bipartisan plan","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"to overhaul border-control laws last June .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"`` It ' s a very big deal ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"and there ' s a path here","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that could get it done , ''","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Cecilia Munoz , the White House ' s director of domestic policy , told the Post.","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Specifically , Boehner ' s initiative would come in the form of simple statement of principles.","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"The central idea is to put forth separate bills","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"dealing with such issues as :","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"This is far different from the view","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"long held by Obama and Democrats","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that immigration could be taken up in a single , sweeping bill.","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"But Obama and Democratic leaders have said","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"they are open to the multiple-bill approach","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"favored by Boehner and key Republicans like Sen. Marco Rubio of Florida .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Rubio ' s backing is crucial for the key bloc of tea party Republicans in both the House and the Senate.","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Fixing the immigration crisis is believed key to the electoral fortunes of both Democrats and Republicans .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"Obama is facing mounting pressure from immigration advocates","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"to halt deportations ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"which are on pace to soon top the 2 million mark during his tenure .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"That ' s more than the George W. Bush administration deported in its entire eight years.","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Republican Party leaders , meanwhile , are convinced","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"that their party must broaden its appeal to Latinos and Asian Americans .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Obama won reelection in 2012 with the support of more than 70 percent of those voters.","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"On Friday , former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg warned Republicans","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"that fixing immigration is essential to their plans","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"to take the Senate in 2014","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"and recapture the White House in 2016 .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"`` If you are against the fastest-growing voting bloc in the country ,","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"you and your party do n't have a future , ''","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Bloomberg said flatly at a forum on immigration Friday with Michigan Republican Gov . Rick Snyder and former Commerce Secretary Carlos Gutierrez ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"who served in President George W. Bush 's administration .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"`` The principles","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"they lay out","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"I ' m sure","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"won ' t satisfy everybody , \"","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Bloomberg said .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"But ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"he added ,","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"`` if we can make some compromises here for the good of the country ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"I think","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"we have a very good chance for the first time in a long time","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"of changing something","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"that is really damaging all of us . ``","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Boehner ' s plan is designed to assuage concerns of conservative Republicans","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"who oppose outright citizenship or amnesty for illegal immigrants","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"who arrived in the country as adults ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"but do not oppose a path toward legalization.","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Alfonso Aguilar , of the Latino Partnership for Conservative Principles , said","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"the question now is whether Democrats would kill any plan toward legalization","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"that does not include citizenship .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"He pointed to a Pew Hispanic Center poll","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"that showed","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"61 percent of immigrant Latinos place legalization higher on their preferences than citizenship ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"the Post reported.","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"Conservative opponents of any compromise on immigration reform had hoped to obstruct the Senate immigration bill in a Senate-House conference committee .","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"However , party leaders appear to be trying to come up with a compromise","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"that circumvents the formal structure of a conference committee ,","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"the Times reported.","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Meanwhile , House immigration hawks are working on an alternative to Boehner 's proposal ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"Breitbart reported .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"On Thursday , aides to House conservatives","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"who oppose the leadership ' s plan","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"gathered in the office of Sen. Jeff Sessions , Republican of Alabama and a fierce opponent of the immigration push ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"to plot a strategy","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"to torpedo it.","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Rep . Raúl R. Labrador , a Republican of Idaho and once a leading immigration negotiator in the House , told the Times","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"it would be a mistake to push forward .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"`` The president has shown","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"he ' s not willing to work with us on immigration , \"","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"Labrador said .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"\" It ' s not worth having a party divided","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"when we have so many issues","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"we can come together on . ``","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Still , many Republicans","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"- especially governors like Snyder -","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"are thought to favor an rapid , comprehensive overhaul of the system .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"`` We need comprehensive immigration reform .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"To be blunt ,","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"we have a dumb system , ''","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"said Snyder ,","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"who described efforts in Michigan","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"to grant visas to immigrants for work .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"it would `` turbo-charge '' the economy in places like Detroit.","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Gutierrez said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"without immigration overhaul ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"`` our workforce down the road does n't grow , ''","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"and argued","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"that there was increasing recognition within the GOP","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that it must be the party of immigration.","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Rep . Kevin McCarthy , R-Calif. , the No . 3 leader in the House , expressed support this week for legalization for many of the immigrants here illegally","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"while Democrats have pressed for a path to citizenship.","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"An unusual coalition of business , labor and evangelicals has lobbied hard for immigration legislation .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"Thomas Donohue , president of the Chamber of Commerce , has said","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"immigration overhaul is a top priority this year .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"Donohue met with Boehner last week.","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"The issue is also crucial to several House Republicans","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"whose districts have seen an increase in Hispanics","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"and who are concerned about their re-election chances.","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"Rep . Mike Coffman , R-Colo. ,","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"who met with Boehner earlier this month ,","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"the speaker is `` very committed to getting it done","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"and getting it done this year .","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"He quoted Boehner as saying ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"`` There 's no good time","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"to do it ,","depth":15},{"id":154,"text":"so let 's just get it done now . ' ''","depth":14}],"relations":[{"parent":309,"left":159,"right":308,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":2,"right":157,"relation":"purpose","